<%- include('../partials/header', { title: 'BMI Explained' }) %>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8 mx-auto">
        <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
            <ol class="breadcrumb">
                <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/info">Info Hub</a></li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item active">BMI</li>
            </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-weight text-primary"></i> Body Mass Index (BMI)</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5>What is BMI?</h5>
                <p>
                    <strong>BMI (Body Mass Index)</strong> is a measure of body fat based on your weight and height.
                    It's widely used by health professionals to categorize weight status.
                </p>

                <h5 class="mt-4">How is BMI Calculated?</h5>
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>Formula:</strong> BMI = weight (kg) / height (m)²
                    <br>
                    <small>Example: 70kg / (1.75m)² = 22.86</small>
                </div>

                <h5 class="mt-4">BMI Categories</h5>
                <table class="table table-bordered">
                    <thead>
                        <tr><th>Category</th><th>BMI Range</th><th>Risk Impact</th></tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr class="table-danger"><td>Underweight</td><td>&lt; 18.5</td><td>⚠️ +15 points</td></tr>
                        <tr class="table-success"><td>Normal</td><td>18.5 – 24.9</td><td>✅ +5 points</td></tr>
                        <tr class="table-warning"><td>Overweight</td><td>25 – 29.9</td><td>⚠️ +25 points</td></tr>
                        <tr class="table-danger"><td>Obese</td><td>≥ 30</td><td>🚨 +40 points</td></tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                    <strong>How BMI affects your Risk Score:</strong> Higher BMI = Higher risk = Higher premium.
                    Maintaining a healthy BMI (18.5-24.9) helps lower your insurance costs.
                </div>

                <h5 class="mt-4">Limitations of BMI</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Doesn't distinguish between muscle and fat</li>
                    <li>May overestimate body fat in athletes</li>
                    <li>May underestimate body fat in older adults</li>
                    <li>Not a direct measure of health</li>
                </ul>

                <a href="/info" class="btn btn-primary mt-3"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Info Hub</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>